Last year China experienced a string of food safety problems including steroid- tainted pork , parasite-infested snails , turbots that contain excessive amount of carcinogens , ducks and hens that were fed cancer-causing Sudan Red dye to make their egg yolks red . 
According to a survey by the State Food and Drug Administration , 65 percent of the respondents worried about the food safety situation in China . 
Food safety has become a major concern of Chinese people . 
The Health Ministry is responsible for supervising such information across the country . 
BEIJING , March 15 ( Xinhua ) 